---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Olle Rönn | Learning Log">
  <section class="hero learning-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Learning Log</p>

    <h1>Learning Log</h1>

    <p class="lead">
      This page summarizes what I have worked on, what I have learned and how my
      technical projects develop over time. It works as a short learning journal
      for my portfolio, GitHub projects and practical technical development.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Log</p>
      <h2>Latest sessions</h2>
      <p>
        Short summaries of recent work on my portfolio, Secure Homelab and other
        technical projects.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="log-list">
      <article class="log-entry current">
        <div class="log-date">
          <span>2026-05-14</span>
          <p>Session 5</p>
        </div>

        <div class="log-content">
          <h3>Completed Secure Homelab version 1</h3>

          <p>
            I completed the first version of my Secure Homelab project. The final
            setup is a Linux-based server environment running Ubuntu Server inside
            VirtualBox, with secure SSH access, firewall rules, fail2ban, Docker
            and several internal services.
          </p>

          <p>
            I installed and verified Docker and Docker Compose, created a shared
            Docker network and configured Portainer, Uptime Kuma, Homepage and
            Nginx as internal Docker-based services. Uptime Kuma was configured
            to monitor the internal services through Docker container names.
          </p>

          <p>
            I also cleaned up the GitHub documentation, added architecture
            diagrams, organized screenshots and wrote a final version 1 summary.
            The documentation now covers the VM setup, networking, installation,
            security configuration, Docker services, lessons learned and the final
            project status.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Learned:</strong> I gained practical experience with Linux
            server administration, SSH hardening, UFW, fail2ban, Docker networking,
            service monitoring and technical documentation.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Result:</strong> Secure Homelab v1 is complete, documented and
            ready to be presented as a portfolio project.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="log-entry">
        <div class="log-date">
          <span>2026-05-12</span>
          <p>Session 4</p>
        </div>

        <div class="log-content">
          <h3>Started Secure Homelab with Ubuntu Server and SSH</h3>

          <p>
            I started my Secure Homelab project by creating a GitHub repository
            with a documentation structure and installing Ubuntu Server in a
            VirtualBox virtual machine.
          </p>

          <p>
            The server was configured with RAM, CPU, virtual disk, NAT networking,
            hostname and a local user. After installation, I updated the system,
            installed basic tools and checked the server networking information.
          </p>

          <p>
            I ran into an issue where SSH from Windows to the VM IP address timed
            out. By checking the SSH service status on the server, I could see
            that SSH itself was running and that the issue was caused by VirtualBox
            NAT. The solution was to configure port forwarding from Windows to the
            Ubuntu server.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Learned:</strong> I gained a better understanding of the
            difference between host and guest systems, how NAT works in VirtualBox,
            why port forwarding is needed for SSH and how to troubleshoot SSH with
            systemctl.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Result:</strong> The first checkpoint was completed. Ubuntu
            Server was installed, updated and reachable via SSH from Windows.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="log-entry">
        <div class="log-date">
          <span>2026-05-11</span>
          <p>Session 3</p>
        </div>

        <div class="log-content">
          <h3>Tested, deployed and published the portfolio</h3>

          <p>
            I performed the final checks of the portfolio, tested the pages in
            both desktop and mobile views and made sure that links, layout and
            content worked as intended.
          </p>

          <p>
            I also deployed the website with Vercel and connected the project to
            GitHub, so the site automatically updates when new changes are pushed
            to the main branch.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Learned:</strong> I gained a better understanding of how GitHub,
            Vercel, the build process and deployment work together in a real web
            project.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Result:</strong> The first version of the portfolio went live
            and can now be updated continuously with new projects, improvements
            and learning logs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="log-entry">
        <div class="log-date">
          <span>2026-05-11</span>
          <p>Session 2</p>
        </div>

        <div class="log-content">
          <h3>Refined the portfolio design and content</h3>

          <p>
            I continued improving the portfolio to make it more complete and
            professional. The focus was on improving the overall feel, making the
            design more minimal and consistent, and making the pages work better
            together.
          </p>

          <p>
            I updated several pages, including the homepage, CV, projects,
            homelab and contact pages. The pages received clearer structure,
            better content and a more consistent presentation of my profile,
            projects and technical direction.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Learned:</strong> I gained a better understanding of how
            content, layout, components and CSS work together in Astro to create
            a more professional and coherent portfolio.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Result:</strong> The portfolio received a clearer design,
            more refined content and a more consistent structure between pages.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="log-entry">
        <div class="log-date">
          <span>2026-05-08</span>
          <p>Session 1</p>
        </div>

        <div class="log-content">
          <h3>Started the portfolio project with Astro</h3>

          <p>
            I set up the foundation for the portfolio website with Astro and
            created the main pages: homepage, CV, projects, learning log, homelab
            and contact.
          </p>

          <p>
            I also started building a shared structure with layout, navigation,
            footer and reusable parts, so the site can grow with more projects
            and documentation over time.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Learned:</strong> I gained a clearer understanding of how
            Astro projects are structured with pages, layouts, components and
            HTML-like structure in `.astro` files.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Result:</strong> The foundation for the portfolio was in
            place and the project could continue with improved design and content.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="learning-focus">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Current focus</p>
      <h2>Portfolio and technical projects</h2>
      <p>
        Secure Homelab v1 is complete and documented. The portfolio is now used
        to present finished projects, ongoing improvements and future technical
        work within infrastructure, cybersecurity, cloud and systems engineering.
      </p>
    </div>

    <a class="focus-card" href="/projects">
      <span class="tag">Project overview</span>
      <h3>View projects</h3>
      <p>
        Go to the projects page to see Secure Homelab, GitHub links, project
        status, technologies and previous technical projects.
      </p>
    </a>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .learning-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5.2vw, 4.2rem);
  }

  .log-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .log-entry {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.35rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.015)),
      var(--surface);
    transition:
      transform 160ms ease,
      border-color 160ms ease,
      background 160ms ease;
  }

  .log-entry:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02)),
      var(--surface-soft);
  }

  .log-entry.current {
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
  }

  .log-date span {
    display: block;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 850;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .log-date p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .log-content h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .log-content p {
    max-width: 780px;
  }

  .learning-focus {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.25fr) minmax(280px, 0.8fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: stretch;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.018)),
      var(--surface);
    transition:
      transform 160ms ease,
      border-color 160ms ease,
      background 160ms ease;
  }

  .learning-focus:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02)),
      var(--surface-soft);
  }

  .learning-focus p {
    max-width: 720px;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .focus-card {
    display: block;
    padding: 1.2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.015)),
      var(--surface);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition:
      transform 160ms ease,
      border-color 160ms ease,
      background 160ms ease;
  }

  .focus-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02)),
      var(--surface-soft);
  }

  .focus-card h3 {
    transition: color 160ms ease;
  }

  .focus-card:hover h3 {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .focus-card p {
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .log-entry {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }

    .learning-focus {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>